# Fixture: fm6-graph-variable-default-graph
# Finding: Failure Mode 6 — GRAPH ?g must not match the default graph
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §13.3; formal semantics §18.5
#
# Hypothesis: GRAPH ?g { ... } matches NAMED graphs only. The default graph
# is never accessible via GRAPH. If the dataset contains only a default graph,
# this query must return zero results. An implementation that represents the
# default graph as an internally named entity may expose it via GRAPH ?g,
# returning solutions when the correct answer is empty.
#
# Divergence: Implementation that includes the default graph in GRAPH ?g
# iteration returns spurious results. Expected: zero results when no named
# graphs exist in the dataset.
# Grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully.

SELECT * WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    ?s ?p ?o .
  }
}
